		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's set up to work with carts from the rest of the world, just a matter of someone having them and a copynes. I'll be getting another big batch of all new (to DB) US carts soon, which will bring it a lot closer to a complete US set.
<br />
<br />It is along the lines of NSRT, with much more extensive info and less "crap". I don't think it will replace GoodNES anymore than NSRT replacing GoodSNES, more of a user preference. In fact, I have been in close contact with Cowering ever since I started this project and have been sharing this data with him. The next GoodNES release will have a lot of [!] in it and corrected headers.
<br />
<br />On a side note, I finally got to working on a guide for the software, I may possibly have it up by the end of the day.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
